race.comment: STAR RAPPER (2) is a horse who has promised plenty from the time he hit the racetrack and while he hasn't lived up to those, dare I say it, raps, this looks one of the most winnable races he has contested. Probably said the same thing two starts ago at Wodonga when he was beaten at $1.45, but only went down narrowly in 72 grade at Morphettville last start and deserves one last chance. WHAT YOU WILL (3) found the step up to 62 grade beyond her last start but was a nice winner the start prior and deserves another chance from a good draw. MISS TOP GUN (13) raced consistently last prep and impressed at her latest jumpout. ACAPPELLA MOON (6) resumes. Consistent mare who has won fresh in the past.
